Source: git-pickdir
Section: vcs
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Debian QA Group <packages@qa.debian.org>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: git-pickdir
Architecture: all
Depends: git (>= 2),
         git-filter-repo,
         ${misc:Depends}
Description: extract subdirectories into a new repo with history flattened to root
 git-pickdir extracts one or more subdirectories from the current Git
 repository into a new repository. Selected paths are flattened to the
 repository root and history is rewritten (using git-filter-repo) so that
 only those paths remain.
 .
 Useful for splitting out parts of a monorepo or creating a new repo from
 selected directories while preserving their history.
